<DocsLayout
  title="Goal mode"
  eyebrow="Capabilities"
  description="Long-running goals with subagents and structured progress."
  prev={{ href: "/docs/mcp/", title: "MCP integration" }}
  next={{ href: "/docs/tui/", title: "TUI" }}
>
  <p>
    Goal mode is gode's pattern for tasks that span many turns: declare a goal, let the
    agent break it into todos, and let it spawn subagents for delimited subtasks while a
    parent agent tracks overall progress.
  </p>

  <h2>The pieces</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>goal</strong> tool — declare and update a structured goal for the session.</li>
    <li><strong>todo</strong> tool — maintain a task list visible to the agent and the UI.</li>
    <li><strong>subagent</strong> tool — spawn a child agent scoped to a single subtask, returning a result the parent uses to continue.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why subagents</h2>
  <p>
    Long tasks accumulate context. Doing everything in one agent forces every irrelevant
    intermediate detail through the same context window. A subagent runs in its own scope
    and returns a summarized result, keeping the parent's context focused on the goal.
  </p>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Goal mode is a workflow, not a separate runtime.</strong> It is built entirely
    out of the same tool registry, event bus, and provider interface as everything else.
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
